eu_initiatives:
The FederBio is involved in the following principal sectors: 
- Internationalisation and promotion of the organic production (EU/national); 
- Traceabilty related to the integrity of organic products along the supply chain, promotion of the products control, market transparency and consumer protection; 
- Education and training.

relevant_communication:
ACTIVITIES AND EVENTS: 
- EXPO "Biodiversity Park and Organic Park" - FederBio is an official partner of Bologna Fiere responsible for the organisation of thematic activities; http://www.federbio.it/Expo_Parco_Biodiversita.php 
- EXPO Forum"Organic can feed the Planet" - FederBio has initiated an International Action Network uniting organic organizations, companies and people working in the organic sector at different levels in debate about the future food security worldwide. The forum is supported by IFOAM Organics International, IFOAM EU, IFOAM AgriBioMediterraneo, ISOFAR, Navdanya International and Bologna Fiere; 
- SANA Bologna (International Exhibition of Organic and Natural Productas) - FederBio is a partner responsibile for the content defintion and events organisation; 
- VinitalyBio Verona (International Exhibition of Organic and Biodynamic Wine) promotion of the certified organic wine; 
- Italian Ministry of Agricultural, Food and Forestry Policies (MIPAAF) - institutional representative within the Agri-food Table. 

RECENT PROJECTS: 
- “Organic Food Organic Mood 2 (OFOM2)” -  promotion of the organic products and European certification mechanisms in: Japan, China and the USA; 
- “BiOrganic_LifeStyle (BIOLS)” -  promotion of the organic products on the European market; 
- "Federbio Integrity Platform"- services related to the integrity of organic products along the supply chain; 
- "Organic Food Organic Mood (OFOM)"- promotion of the Italian organic products and European certification mechanisms in: Japan, China and the USA;  
- "Made in Italy" - promotion of the quality certification related to religious, organic and 'Made in Italy' products; 
- Project related to dissemination, promotion and protection of the organic food products, cosmetics, integrators, and similar, as a support to the Italian companies in the South Korea; 
- "Bio Accademy"- the specialised school in organic and biodynamic agriculture. 

